nt("ul",null,r.default.createElement("li",null,"A permanent scientific base on the Moon - imagine your child doing a PhD at Moon Base Alpha, joining the 1,000 other scientists there for a two year stay"),r.default.createElement("li",null,"A Mars colony - you regularly exchange video messages with your friend who sold his house to move to another planet and start a new life"),r.default.createElement("li",null,"Space tourism - you can see Earth from space for the price of a premium airline ticket"),r.default.createElement("li",null,"Probes and landers to destinations which have tremendous scientific value - you can watch high-resolution documentaries about Enceladus' underground oceans or Titan's cryovolcanoes"),r.default.createElement("li",null,"And a lot more...")),r.default.createElement("h2",null,"How it works"),r.default.createElement("p",null,"Now is the time to ask: how is it even possible??? How can Starship achieve such a low cost access to space? The key word is:"),r.default.createElement("p",null,r.default.createElement("em",null,"Reusability.")),r.default.createElement("p",null,"Rocket stages are usually single use: they are thrown into the ocean after delivering their payloads to orbit. With Falcon 9,"," ",r.default.createElement("strong",null,"SpaceX has already proven that landing rocket boosters and reusing them is possible ",r.default.createElement("em",null,"and")," profitable.")," ","However, SpaceX has only reused first stages so far, which means that a lot of costly parts must still be manufactured for each launch."),r.default.createElement("figure",null,r.default.createElement("img",{src:l+"reuse.jpg",alt:"Two Falcon Heavy boosters landing at once"}),r.default.createElement("figcaption",null,r.default.createElement("em",null,"Two Falcon 9 boosters landing simultaneously"))),r.default.createElement("p",null,r.default.createElement("strong",null,"Contrary to Falcon 9, Starship is big enough and has enough fuel margins that it will be possible to recover and reuse both stages"),", making it the first 100% reusable rocket system in history. With airplane-like reliability, the only real cost is the fuel - about ~$500,000 for a fully-fueled Starship. Amortize the manufacturing cost of both stages over 100 launches, add some margins and you get the $5,000,000/100 tons or $50/kg price tag to Low Earth orbit."),r.default.createElement("h2",null,"Timelines"),r.default.createElement("p",null,"The best thing is:"," ",r.default.createElement("strong",null,"all of this is going to happen way sooner than you think"),". The SpaceX team is hell-bent on landing a Starship on Mars by 2024. To achieve this goal, they are moving really, really fast. Here is an updated timeline of what has happened and is happening right now regarding Starship development:"),r.default.createElement("h3",null,"Phase 1 - Raptor engine development - DONE"),r.default.createElement("p",null,"The Raptor engine is the rocket engine that powers Starship. They are"," ",r.default.createElement("em",null,"really, really high tech")," by rocket engine standards and the rocket will have more than 30 of them. As it's the single most complicated system in the rocket, so development began around 2012. After a lot of testing,"," ",r.default.createElement("strong",null,"Raptor has entered mass production in 2019.")),r.default.createElement("figure",null,r.default.createElement("img",{src:l+"raptor.png",alt:"A raptor engine firing"})),r.default.createElement("h3",null,"Phase 2 - Starhopper low-fidelity prototype - DONE"),r.default.createElement("p",null,"To test its Raptor engine in real flight conditions, SpaceX contracted a water tower company to rapidly assemble a working Starship prototype. This prototype made hops (the highest at 150 meters)"," ",r.default.createElement("strong",null,"and allowed SpaceX to validate the engine control and landing algorithms"),"."),r.default.createElement("figure",null,r.default.createElement("img",{src:l+"starhopper.jpg",alt:"Starhopper hopping"})),r.default.createElement("h3",null,"Phase 3 - Starship prototypes - HAPPENING RIGHT NOW"),r.default.createElement("p",null,"The next step is to test Starship in Earth's upper atmosphere, to validate a heat shielding technology and to prove that second stages can also be safely landed and reused."," ",r.default.createElement("strong",null,"SpaceX is currently building two high fidelity Starship prototypes: one in Florida, one in Texas.")," ","The first team to reach orbit and come back on land is the winner."),r.default.createElement("figure",null,r.default.createElement("img",{src:l+"florida.jpg",alt:"Starship prototype in Florida"}),r.default.createElement("figcaption",null,r.default.createElement("em",null,"Starship prototype in Florida"))),r.default.createElement("figure",null,r.default.createElement("img",{src:l+"texas.jpg",alt:"Starship prototype in Texas"}),r.default.createElement("figcaption",null,r.default.createElement("em",null,"Starship prototype in Texas"))),r.default.createElement("h3",null,"Phase 4 - First commercial launch - 2021"),r.default.createElement("p",null,"SpaceX is already in talks with three potential customers for a commercial satellite launch in 2021. This will be a big milestone, because"," ",r.default.createElement("strong",null,"it will mean that Starship is already cheaper and better than the Falcon 9"),". Also, it will make the rocket pay for itself (which is an achievement, considering the size of the thing)."),r.default.createElement("figure",null,r.default.createElement("img",{src:l+"2021.png",alt:"Starship skyrocketing"})),r.default.createElement("h3",null,"Phase 5 - First landing on Mars - 2022"),r.default.createElement("p",null,"While Starship will be developed to enter mass production and execute most SpaceX missions, two cargo Starships will be retired and launched towards Mars."," ",r.default.createElement("strong",null,"The goal will be to prove that Earth landing technologies also work on Mars.")),r.d